<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-59-1247 </DOCNO><TEXT>The widespread availability of computed tomography (CT) has curtailedthe use of conventional radiographic tomography considerably, but therestill remain a few applications in both adult and pediatric radiographyand some of the pediatric uses will be presented here. Radiographic tomography,of course, remains an important imaging tool in centers where CT is notavailable.</TEXT></DOC>